{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reduce 5 week wait for first Universal Credit payment to 2 weeks.",
        "additional_details": "\"Arrears for UC claimants are almost 6 times the average arrears of a Housing Benefit claimant (\u00a3162) \u2013 the UC average is \u00a3938.\" \r\nPeabody.\r\n\r\n\"Our evidence has consistently shown the 5 week wait to be one of the most problematic features of UC.\" \r\nCAB Scotland.\r\n\r\n\"Tenants claiming Universal Credit at July 2019 had seen a much bigger average increase in rent\u00a0arrears since roll-out began than Housing Benefit tenants.\" \r\nRiverside Group.",
        "background": "Reduce the wait for claimants first Universal Credit payment from 5 weeks to a maximum of 2 weeks. It has been proven & evidenced by numerous sources that the wait causes severe financial hardship leading to debt, rent arrears, homelessness & mental health problems.",
